Several times now have hidden rules been brought up to upcoming guilds and those rules that come up are for one thing. To insure that the progress of those guilds are slowed. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You are wrong. Do you think that there is a giant 'uber' guild conspiracy to keep content from the other guilds on the server? Ok, lets imagine if this was true. <br>
<br>
Why, then, if the goal of the big guilds was to keep the little guy down, why would guilds ever leave a rotation? That is a simple, and easy way to delay content. It would only take BotS or Tindi an extra 40 minutes of their day to zap the AoW on their turn, if that. <br>
<br>
Firstly, anything at the velious level is now so far below the radar of &quot;uber&quot; that it may as well be old world content. United necros could be permafarming nagafen for all anyone cares, really, and that progression holds, minus the rotations, all the way to the highest end game. You think a guild in Vex Thal gives a flying rats ass if a mob they have no interest in is permafarmed? Hell no. <br>
<br>
There is no &quot;i'm so uber&quot; conspiracy. Just isn't. People who think there is have one of two problems; dillusions of grandeur or a thin grasp of reality. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
This is not right and is wrong because not one person said, ok you cant do this, to the ones who tried first.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This argument is flawed on the basis that it does not account for the fact that conditions can change with time. The reason that no one said &quot;you can't do this&quot; to the first people to do it, is that there <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>were</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> no other people on the rotation. Now that there are, there is a level of courtesy that must be maintained between guilds. Saying that the first guilds to kill the AoW didn't need to be courteous is at worst misdirection; at best, a misunderstanding of the reasons for courtesy. If I was the only one in the world with a car, I wouldn't have to signal before changing lanes, for example. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The old argument that no one else was doing it so it was open doesn't mean much cause when two guilds got on then that went out the door. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This statement weakens, not strengthens, your arguement, because it's true. <br>
<br>
As soon as another guild killed the AoW, the first guild in established a rotation with them; that is, began to be courteous to others on the rotation. If there are no others on a rotation, there is no one to be courteous to. Arguably, it's not even a rotation. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Now I know that posting here in this forum might piss off the admins but not everyone can post in the guild rep forum and others have a right to say things. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yeah, look at me, I'm spitting angry at you. Die die die. /yawn. <br>
<br>
Not hardly. The post was moved there because it was going to turn into a flame festival if not talked about by the leaders/reps of the guilds. Quite honestly, people talk differantly in differant forums. And in the reps forum, people don't flame (or at least try not to).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
As I have said the top guilds on this server earned their way and respect thru hard way and dedication to things. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Sure did. Good job to those who cleared the way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Don't you think that those new guilds coming up should have the right to the same respect and be proud of winning on those uber mobs like you did? <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No one is saying that we can't get on the rotation. All that is being discussed is how to make that entry as simple for the people trying to get on as possible, while making sure that those who have gone before do not get disrupted so badly as to make it *not* worthwhile to let new guilds on. <br>
<br>
That is in *everyone's* interest.<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
